Intel C compiler - compiler optimization, developed by Intel for x86 processors families, x86-64 and IA-64.

Components Intel C Compiler Professional Edition. Threading and optimization in the Intel compiler and libraries professional publishing one of the best decisions for the compilation of the latest high performance applications for multicore processors.

* Interprocedural Optimization
* Automatic parallelization of code
* Trace
* Optimization of the profile information of light (Profile Guided Optimization in English)

The disadvantages of a compiler can be attributed to the partial incompatibility gnu-extensions of C language (supported by GCC compiler), which can cause problems when compiling certain programs.
